01:52:23,792 --> 01:52:25,191
Without what?

1503
01:52:25,561 --> 01:52:27,290
Them smearing yours first?

1504
01:52:27,630 --> 01:52:31,361
What do they have? Pictures of you
and Matt Reynolds with your pants down?

1505
01:52:33,736 --> 01:52:34,794
You have any proof?

1506
01:52:35,471 --> 01:52:37,200
The proof had his throat slit.

1507
01:52:38,574 --> 01:52:40,735
So far, you're not denying it.

1508
01:52:42,077 --> 01:52:44,045
l won't dignify this with answers.

1509
01:52:44,246 --> 01:52:46,714
Now if you gentlemen will excuse me...

1510
01:52:46,916 --> 01:52:50,750
...l have a press conference for Jack
Vincennes that l have to prepare for.

1511
01:53:01,096 --> 01:53:04,998
Unless you came to wipe my ass,
l believe we're through.

1512
01:53:09,672 --> 01:53:14,006
Don't pull that good cop-bad cop crap.
l practically invented it.

1513
01:53:14,777 --> 01:53:16,972
So what if some homo actor is dead.

1514
01:53:17,179 --> 01:53:20,273
Boys, girls, ten of them
get off the bus to L.A. everyday.

1515
01:53:28,190 --> 01:53:29,487
Pull him off me! !

1516
01:53:29,692 --> 01:53:30,624
l don't know how.

1517
01:53:34,530 --> 01:53:38,432
l know you think you're the A-number-one
hotshot, but here's the juice.

1518
01:53:38,634 --> 01:53:41,102
lf l kill you, 10 lawyers
will take your place tomorrow.

1519
01:53:41,303 --> 01:53:43,134
They just won't come on a bus.

1520
01:53:57,052 --> 01:53:58,144
Okay!

1521
01:53:59,488 --> 01:54:01,718
Dudley and Patchett, they....

1522
01:54:02,791 --> 01:54:03,951
Oh, my God!

1523
01:54:04,159 --> 01:54:06,184
l wouldn't play ball so they set me up!

1524
01:54:06,395 --> 01:54:08,488
l gave in!
But the kid heard everything...

1525
01:54:09,999 --> 01:54:10,966
...so they killed him.

1526
01:54:11,166 --> 01:54:12,155
Why?

1527
01:54:12,534 --> 01:54:15,970
-What are Dudley and Patchett up to?
-Taking over Mickey Cohen's rackets.

1528
01:54:16,171 --> 01:54:20,107
Because of those pictures
l couldn't prosecute them!

1529
01:54:20,509 --> 01:54:21,874
Oh, Jesus!

1530
01:54:22,077 --> 01:54:23,009
Help me up!

1531
01:54:32,154 --> 01:54:34,315
ls that how you ran
the good cop-bad cop?

1532
01:54:36,859 --> 01:54:38,019
Patchett?

1533
01:55:13,462 --> 01:55:16,124
Looks like his bodyguard
had a conflict of interest.

1534
01:55:22,571 --> 01:55:23,936
Suicide note.

1535
01:55:24,139 --> 01:55:28,576
Says he killed Jack because Jack had
figured out his pornography scam.

1536
01:55:28,811 --> 01:55:30,972
Slicing himself open wasn't his idea.

1537
01:55:32,414 --> 01:55:33,881
2 of his fingers
are broken.

1538
01:55:34,083 --> 01:55:34,981
They held him there.

1539
01:55:37,219 --> 01:55:38,151
Or drugged him.

1540
01:55:41,590 --> 01:55:43,387
Dudley's tying up his loose ends.

1541
01:55:44,259 --> 01:55:45,556
Patchett's dead.

1542
01:55:45,761 --> 01:55:47,422
He sent you after me.

1543
01:55:49,098 --> 01:55:50,258
Lynn.

1544
01:55:51,433 --> 01:55:52,627
West Hollywood Sheriff.

1545
01:55:52,835 --> 01:55:55,668
-They're closer than we are.
-l'll get the car. Keys!

1546
01:56:03,178 --> 01:56:05,772
We took her to the station
for safekeeping.

1547
01:56:06,782 --> 01:56:10,343
Hold her as Joan Smith.
And no one sees her unless l okay it.

1548
01:56:11,120 --> 01:56:12,815
Someone worked her over.

1549
01:56:13,021 --> 01:56:14,682
She wouldn't say who.

1550
01:56:19,862 --> 01:56:21,454
See you, Exley.

1551
01:56:24,700 --> 01:56:26,190
We should talk to Lynn.

1552
01:56:27,202 --> 01:56:28,362
You do it.

1553
01:56:29,037 --> 01:56:30,197
What will you do?

1554
01:56:33,475 --> 01:56:35,375
l'm going to talk to Sid Hudgens.

1555
01:56:36,078 --> 01:56:38,774
Compliment him on his
performance at the Victory Motel.

1556
01:56:38,981 --> 01:56:41,211
Remember, Bud, we need evidence.

1557
01:56:42,384 --> 01:56:43,874
l'll get the evidence.

1558
01:56:56,398 --> 01:56:57,387
Are you okay?

1559
01:57:00,169 --> 01:57:01,158
You okay?

1560
01:57:11,847 --> 01:57:13,838
Bud hates himself for what he did.

1561
01:57:15,083 --> 01:57:17,074
l know how he feels.

1562
01:57:19,421 --> 01:57:22,254
l need to know what you
can give me on Dudley Smith.

1563
01:57:24,359 --> 01:57:26,759
He's a police captain
in business with Patchett.

1564
01:57:27,429 --> 01:57:28,919
l've never heard of him.

1565
01:57:33,202 --> 01:57:34,760
Do you have a place to stay?

1566
01:57:36,538 --> 01:57:38,028
l'll be okay.

1567
01:57:44,613 --> 01:57:46,945
Nobody goes in without official l.D.!

1568
01:57:51,720 --> 01:57:53,381
He's okay. Let him through.

1569
01:57:56,959 --> 01:57:58,290
What happened?

1570
01:57:58,894 --> 01:58:01,920
Someone beat him to death,
and stole a bunch of files.

1571
01:58:02,130 --> 01:58:04,121
Must have dug up garbage
on the wrong guy.

1572
01:58:04,566 --> 01:58:06,534
We got it narrowed down
to 1000 suspects.

1573
01:58:07,803 --> 01:58:09,065
Sergeant White...

1574
01:58:10,072 --> 01:58:11,699
...dispatch got a call for you.

1575
01:58:11,907 --> 01:58:14,933
Lieutenant Exley wants you
to meet him at the Victory Motel.

1576
01:58:48,944 --> 01:58:50,502
You wanted to meet here?

1577
01:58:52,614 --> 01:58:55,606
-You called it. l thought Hudgens was--
-Hudgens is dead.

1578
01:59:07,029 --> 01:59:08,621
Let's get out of here.

1579
01:59:16,038 --> 01:59:17,369
lt's too late.

1580
02:00:06,922 --> 02:00:09,049
You figured it was a set-up
but came anyway?

1581
02:00:09,257 --> 02:00:11,248
A lot of bad stuff happened here.

1582
02:00:11,760 --> 02:00:14,024
lt's as good a place
as any for it to end.

1583
02:00:24,272 --> 02:00:25,364
Clip.

1584
02:00:30,445 --> 02:00:33,209
All l ever wanted was to
measure up to my father.

1585
02:00:34,282 --> 02:00:35,214
Now's your chance.

1586
02:00:37,953 --> 02:00:39,784
He died in the line of duty, didn't he?

1587
02:02:39,441 --> 02:02:40,408
Goddamn it!

1588
02:03:40,802 --> 02:03:41,530
You okay?

1589
02:03:42,404 --> 02:03:43,632
Yeah.

1590
02:04:02,157 --> 02:04:04,148
Come on. Easy.

1591
02:04:10,932 --> 02:04:11,830
Move!

1592
02:04:34,522 --> 02:04:36,012
Rollo Tomasi.

1593
02:04:39,461 --> 02:04:40,792
Who is he?

1594
02:04:41,630 --> 02:04:42,756
You are.

1595
02:04:45,033 --> 02:04:46,864
You're the guy who gets away with it.

1596
02:04:50,972 --> 02:04:52,098
Jack knew it.

1597
02:04:52,307 --> 02:04:53,638
And so do l.

1598
02:05:19,334 --> 02:05:21,063
Are you going to shoot me...

1599
02:05:22,337 --> 02:05:23,395
...or arrest me?

1600
02:05:29,744 --> 02:05:31,075
Good lad.

1601
02:05:31,846 --> 02:05:33,780
Always the politician.

1602
02:05:34,416 --> 02:05:36,247
Let me do the talking.

1603
02:05:36,851 --> 02:05:39,911
After l'm done,
they'll make you Chief of Detectives.

1604
02:06:07,782 --> 02:06:09,443
Hold up your badge...

1605
02:06:09,784 --> 02:06:11,718
...so they'll know you're a policeman.

1606
02:07:02,270 --> 02:07:05,103
You think you can talk
your way out of this, Lieutenant?

1607
02:07:07,709 --> 02:07:08,869
No...

1608
02:07:09,144 --> 02:07:10,736
...but l can tell the truth.

1609
02:07:11,713 --> 02:07:13,613
During our investigation...

1610
02:07:14,716 --> 02:07:17,810
...of events surrounding
the Nite Owl case...

1611
02:07:18,887 --> 02:07:22,323
...Jack Vincennes, Bud White
and l learned the following:

1612
02:07:23,057 --> 02:07:25,525
Your golden boy's
throwing his whole life away.

1613
02:07:25,727 --> 02:07:27,285
The 3 Nite Owl suspects...

1614
02:07:28,229 --> 02:07:30,663
...while guilty of
kidnapping and rape...

1615
02:07:31,499 --> 02:07:34,491
...were innocent of the
multiple homicides at the Nite Owl.

1616
02:07:35,837 --> 02:07:37,805
The gunmen were most likely...

1617
02:07:38,006 --> 02:07:42,807
...Los Angeles police officers
Michael Breuning and William Carlisle...

1618
02:07:43,011 --> 02:07:44,501
...and a third man...

1619
02:07:45,180 --> 02:07:48,843
...who may or may not have been
Captain Dudley Smith.

1620
02:07:49,918 --> 02:07:51,351
The objective:

1621
02:07:52,353 --> 02:07:54,981
The elimination of
another police officer...

1622
02:07:55,190 --> 02:07:57,021
...Richard Stensland...

1623
02:07:57,926 --> 02:08:02,863
...who, along with former LAPD officer
Leland ''Buzz'' Meeks...

1624
02:08:03,932 --> 02:08:07,698
...also committed multiple homicides
on behalf of Captain Smith...

1625
02:08:08,369 --> 02:08:09,927
...and then betrayed him...

1626
02:08:10,205 --> 02:08:12,435
...over 25 pounds of heroin...

1627
02:08:13,541 --> 02:08:15,372
...the retrieval of which...

1628
02:08:15,710 --> 02:08:18,702
...was the ultimate motivation
behind the Nite Owl killings.

1629
02:08:21,950 --> 02:08:25,215
Beginning with the incarceration
of Mickey Cohen...

1630
02:08:25,620 --> 02:08:30,557
...Capt. Smith has been assuming control
of organized crime in Los Angeles.

1631
02:08:32,393 --> 02:08:36,124
This includes the assassinations
of Mickey Cohen lieutenants...

1632
02:08:36,731 --> 02:08:39,894
...the systematic blackmail
of city officials...

1633
02:08:41,469 --> 02:08:46,065
...and the murders of Susan Lefferts,
Pierce Patchett, Sid Hudgens...

1634
02:08:47,475 --> 02:08:49,568
...and Sergeant Jack Vincennes.

1635
02:08:52,814 --> 02:08:55,647
Captain Smith admitted as much to me...

1636
02:08:56,251 --> 02:08:58,151
...before l shot him...

1637
02:08:58,586 --> 02:09:00,315
...at the Victory Motel.

1638
02:09:02,590 --> 02:09:03,648
That's it.

1639
02:09:05,994 --> 02:09:07,154
Well...

1640
02:09:08,596 --> 02:09:10,655
...the press will have
a field day.

1641
02:09:12,267 --> 02:09:13,734
Christ!

1642
02:09:13,935 --> 02:09:16,233
lt'll stain the Department for years.

1643
02:09:16,437 --> 02:09:17,335
Decades.

1644
02:09:18,673 --> 02:09:21,267
lf we can get the kid to play ball...

1645
02:09:22,277 --> 02:09:24,108
...who's to say what happened?

1646
02:09:25,179 --> 02:09:27,670
Maybe Dudley Smith died a hero.

1647
02:09:27,949 --> 02:09:30,509
-Good idea.
-lf we get the press to play.

1648
02:09:38,359 --> 02:09:41,021
Want to tell me what
you're smiling about?

1649
02:09:46,534 --> 02:09:47,796
A hero.

1650
02:09:48,369 --> 02:09:50,098
How'd he know what we said?

1651
02:09:50,305 --> 02:09:51,966
He couldn't have heard us.

1652
02:09:55,810 --> 02:09:57,641
ln this situation...

1653
02:09:58,046 --> 02:09:59,980
...you'll need more than one.

1654
02:10:06,888 --> 02:10:11,825
lt is my pleasure to present this award
to Detective Lieutenant Edmund Exley...

1655
02:10:12,393 --> 02:10:14,486
...two-time Medal of Valor recipient.

1656
02:10:24,672 --> 02:10:28,665
Next year the LAPD
will move into its new facility.

1657
02:10:29,010 --> 02:10:30,705
With leaders like Edmund Exley...

1658
02:10:30,912 --> 02:10:34,040
...the image of fat cops stealing apples
will be left behind...

1659
02:10:34,248 --> 02:10:38,184
...and Los Angeles will finally
have the police force it deserves.

1660
02:10:52,100 --> 02:10:54,227
You just couldn't resist.

1661
02:10:54,469 --> 02:10:57,029
They're using me.
So for a while, l'm using them.

1662
02:10:59,040 --> 02:11:00,098
Come on.

1663
02:11:35,076 --> 02:11:36,373
Thanks for the push.

1664
02:11:58,132 --> 02:12:00,157
Congratulations, Lieutenant Exley.

1665
02:12:03,504 --> 02:12:05,597
Some men get the world...

1666
02:12:06,107 --> 02:12:09,668
...others get ex-hookers
and a trip to Arizona.

